# NestJS API patterns

## Module structure
Every module must have: module.ts, controller.ts, service.ts,
dto/ folder, entities/ folder, index.ts, and a spec.ts test file.

## DTOs
Always use class-validator decorators. Every controller input needs a DTO.
```typescript
import { IsString, IsEmail, MinLength } from 'class-validator';
export class CreateUserDto {
  @IsEmail() email: string;
  @IsString() @MinLength(8) password: string;
}
```

## Guards
Protect all authenticated routes with JwtAuthGuard.
Use RolesGuard for RBAC (User, InstitutionalAdmin, Support, SystemAdmin).

## Error handling
Use NestJS built-in HttpException classes. Never throw raw JS errors.
```typescript
throw new NotFoundException(`User ${id} not found`);
throw new UnauthorizedException('Invalid credentials');
throw new BadRequestException('Validation failed');
```

## Async jobs
All browser automation and long tasks — BullMQ queue.
Return job_id immediately. Push status updates via WebSocket.

## Database
TypeORM with parameterized queries only.
No raw SQL string interpolation. Ever.
